And how would we denote speed then,

00:00:36.958 --> 00:00:38.397
if S is distance?

00:00:38.397 --> 00:00:40.725
Well speed is the rate
of change of distance

00:00:40.725 --> 00:00:42.263
with respect to time.

00:00:42.263 --> 00:00:43.813
So our speed would be

00:00:43.813 --> 00:00:46.133
the rate of distance with respect to time.

00:00:46.133 --> 00:00:48.893
The rate of change of
distance with respect to time.

00:00:48.893 --> 00:00:52.295
So this is going to be our speed.

00:00:52.295 --> 00:00:53.734
So now that we got our notation,

00:00:53.734 --> 00:00:55.073
S is the distance,

00:00:55.073 --> 00:00:58.331
the derivative of S with
respect to time is speed.

00:00:58.331 --> 00:01:01.047
We can say the speed which is d,

00:01:01.047 --> 00:01:01.880
capital S,

00:01:01.880 --> 00:01:03.105
dt,

